content:
One of the most critical steps we can take to curb gun violence in America is repealing the law the NRA has called its “#1 priority,” but you’ve probably never heard of: the Protection of Lawful Commerce in Arms Act (PLCAA). This 2005 law provides the gun industry with an unprecedented immunity from liability that no other industry enjoys, and which has denied families their day in court. I introduced a bill to end this legal loophole and ensure the gun industry is held accountable when it acts with negligent disregard for public safety.

Join me and representatives from Guns Down America, Giffords, and Survivors Empowered on Monday, June 21st at 8:30pm ET for a LIVE virtual discussion on why must repeal PLCAA, hold the gun industry accountable, and give victims and survivors of gun violence their day in court. Register here: https://giffords-org.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_7sRG8XIGQFS2oSy4Ai3__A

Questions? Leave them in the comments below 👇

As President Trump incited an attack on our nation’s Capitol in order to overturn the results of a free and fair election, his Administration delayed the National Guard response.

At 1:34 PM, Mayor Bowser called for additional forces. She would be followed soon after by Capitol Police, D.C. Homeland Security and D.C. police. The responsibility for this delayed response to this serious threat to national security and the foundations of our democracy lies squarely on former President Trump and former Acting Secretary of Defense Christopher Miller. The American people deserve full accountability, transparency and corrective action.
